The paper discusses the use of scientific literature to model scholarly discourse and focuses on scientometrics, which involves the analysis of scientific publications and citations. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Digital Libraries (cs.DL), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Cybersecurity (cs.CY), or Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-categories. The paper's emphasis on analyzing document sets and measuring intellectual organization also aligns with the topics covered in these sub-categories.
